      "solution": "n = gets.to_i\nx=''\nn.times do\n    num = gets.chomp\n    y = num.tr('01245679','')\n    r = num.to_i * y.length\n    x += \"#{r} \"\nend\n\nputs x.strip\n",
      "statement": "A number is said to have one or more Roman triplets if, once converted to a Roman numeral, it features three instances in a row of one or more symbols.\n\nExample:\n\n* <<36>> is translated as <<XXXVI>>, therefore it has <<1>> triplet.\n* <<1328>> is translated as <<MCCCXXVIII>>, therefore it has <<2>> triplets.\n* <<299>> is translated as <<CCXCIX>>, but since the three <<C>> are not together, it has <<0>> triplets.\n\nFor more information on how Roman numerals work, see: https://www.britannica.com/topic/Roman-numeral",
