    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">A number is said to have one or more Roman triplets if, once converted to a Roman numeral, it features three instances in a row of one or more symbols.<br><br>Example:<br><br>* <strong>36</strong> is translated as <strong>XXXVI</strong>, therefore it has <strong>1</strong> triplet.<br>* <strong>1328</strong> is translated as <strong>MCCCXXVIII</strong>, therefore it has <strong>2</strong> triplets.<br>* <strong>299</strong> is translated as <strong>CCXCIX</strong>, but since the three <strong>C</strong> are not together, it has <strong>0</strong> triplets.<br><br>For more information on how Roman numerals work, see: https://www.britannica.com/topic/Roman-numeral</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> An integer <var>N</var> for the amount of numbers to convert.<br><strong>Next <var>N</var> lines:</strong> A number <var>R</var></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">A single line containing each number, multiplied by the amount of triplets it contains.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">0 &lt; <strong>N</strong> &lt; 1000<br>0 &lt; <strong>R</strong> &lt; 4000</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">3\n1\n36\n1328</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-in